public abstract class AbstractProgressListener

cancel

public void cancel()
Description copied from interface: ProgressListener
Invoking this method to cancel the transfer.
This method, togethe with ProgressListener.isCancelled(), provides a functionality that a user can cancel a transfer. To accomplish this function, the concrete implementation of opensftp-api should invoke the isCancelled() method to determine whether continue the transfer or not.
